This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) category as it deals with recommendation algorithms. It could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category as it mentions state of the art model-based collaborative approaches. Additionally, the consideration of time in the proposed approach suggests it could belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category. The use of popularity as a signal could also place it in the Social and Economic Networks (cs.SOC) category. Finally, the mention of experimental evaluation suggests it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.DL) category as well.
